@startuml
title Subsidiary Ledger Transaction Lifecycle

hide empty description

state Draft as "Draft\nCreated, details are editable."
state Submitted as "Submitted\nAwaiting internal authorization."
state Approved as "Approved\nAuthorized for posting/processing."
state Posted as "Posted\nRecorded in the Subsidiary Ledger."
state Reconciled   as "Reconciled\nConfirmed against GL or external data."
state Voided   as "Voided\nCanceled and removed from flow."

' Initial State
[*] --> Draft : Create

' Submission and Authorization Flow
Draft --> Submitted : Submit for Approval
Draft --> Voided : Cancel Transaction

Submitted --> Approved : Authorize
Submitted --> Draft : Return for Edit

' Posting
Approved --> Posted : Execute Posting

' Reconciliation (The key difference for SLT)
Posted --> Reconciled : Reconcile with GL/Bank

' Error/Reversal Flow
Approved --> Voided : Void Pre-Posting
Posted --> Voided : Void After Posting (Reversal Required)

' Revert for Correction
Voided --> Draft : Reopen/Re-enter
Reconciled --> Posted : Un-reconcile (High-Privilege Action)

@enduml